<CONTENT id="_3793149_1"><TITLE value="Session 9"/><TITLECOLOR value="#000000"/><DESCRIPTION
   value=""/><BODY><TEXT>&lt;h4&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-46884691_1" alt="" width="519" height="304" style="border: 0px solid #000000;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;&#xd;
&lt;h4&gt;Introduction&lt;/h4&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;During this session we will be examining various ways of protecting an organisation's data.&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;Typically the organisation's data is one of the most valuable assets owned by the organisation.&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;Protection includes preventing theft, unauthorised access, and unauthorised changes or corruption.&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xd;
&lt;h5&gt;News&lt;/h5&gt;&#xd;
&lt;ol&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2024/why-can-t-i-get-a-graduate-job-in-cyber-security-.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM23519" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Why can’t I get a graduate job in cyber security? | Information Age | ACS&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;Does this apply to you as a potential TAFE graduate?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt; DISCUSS with the lecturer!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://australiancybersecuritymagazine.com.au/paying-cyber-ransoms-still-lands-organisations-in-hot-water/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Paying cyber-ransoms still lands organisations in hot water - Australian Cyber Security Magazine&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://australiancybersecuritymagazine.com.au/new-national-cyber-security-coordinator-announced/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;New National Cyber Security Coordinator announced - Australian Cyber Security Magazine&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/ol&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;h5 id="anonymous_element_24"&gt;Topic&lt;/h5&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;During this session we will continue to examine methods used to protect an organisation's data.&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;We will consider various policies, tools and systems for cyber protection.&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;These include&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;ul&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;Host Intrusion Detection Systems,&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;Cryptography, and&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;various means of obfuscating data&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/ul&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Out of Session Activity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;Review the various methods for protecting data in your own personal or organisational use.&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;Think about how these compare to what was discussed during this session.&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;h5&gt;Portfolio Tasks&lt;/h5&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;Check assessments tab.&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;Complete outstanding work&lt;/div&gt;</TEXT><TYPE
